        <h2>What is Radon?</h2>
        <p>Radon is a colorless, odorless, radioactive gas that occurs naturally when uranium in soil, rock, and water breaks down. It's the second leading cause of lung cancer in the United States, responsible for about 21,000 deaths each year.</p>

        <h3>Why Test for Radon?</h3>
        <p>The EPA recommends that all homes be tested for radon, regardless of geographic location or foundation type. Radon can enter your home through:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Cracks in foundation walls and floors</li>
          <li>Gaps around service pipes</li>
          <li>Construction joints</li>
          <li>Crawl spaces</li>
          <li>Well water (in some cases)</li>
        </ul>

